                              GRID START

Typed in by ???. Edited by PARASITE.


Welcome to GRID START, a challenge to your driving skills and the speed of
your reflexes under pressure.  You are an aspirant to the ultimate accolade
of being the Grand Prix Champion of the Professional class.  You can
however attempt the championship of the Novice and Amateur sections first.
You will be competing against 23 other cars and the competition is going to
be tough.

You are driving a six gear Formula 1 car.  The secret of driving a racing
car is in the rapid changing of gears, the instinctive knowledge of the
maximum speed at which a partiuclar ben can be safely taken and the
opportune use of the brakes and the boost.

THE GRAND PRIX CIRCUITS ARE:
SILVERSTONE
BRANDS HATCH
AUTODROMO HERMANDS
OSTERREICHRING
HOCKENHEIM

Each circuit is faithfully reproduced.

You are advised to do several practic laps before entering the competition.
Learn the course throughly so that you know instinctively which bend to
expect.  Learn to position your car to take advantage of the bend.  Your
car is fitted with Boost.  There is only a limited amount of Boost
available.  Use it sparingly to overtake and to get ahead and stay ahead.

INSTRUCTIONS:
Press Joystick Fir Button (F.B.) to exit the title screen and load the rest
of the program.  You will be shown six tracks and the menu.  You can move
the highlight using the J/S.

SKILL
NOVICE,AMATEUR or PROFESSIONAL.  Press F.F. to change the skill level.

TRACK
The track number will change when the F.B. is pressed.

PRACTICE
Select PRACTICE or COMPETE by pressing F.B.

DONE
When satisfied, press F.B. to start the game.

COMPETE
You can select the track order.  When you have completed the required
number of laps the high score table will show your time, points and
championship placing.  Press F.B. to display the track screen and make the
next track choics.

PRACTICE
You can practice any track for as long as you like.  You may quit by
pressing ESC key and return to the track display screen.  The correct
selection of gears is very important.  You may have to change gears two or
three times to take a bend correctly.  Learn To apply minimum abount of
braking at the right time.

CONTROLS:
             Firebutton OFF                Firebutton ON

               Accelerate                    Change Up

         Left              Right      Left               Right

               Brake                         Change Down

Learn to apply the gears quickly as pressing the FIRE BUTTON also gives the
BOOST.
